This paper deals with the use of image processing and neural networks for robot navigation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also heavily relies on computer vision techniques for trajectory segmentation, which suggests that it could also be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of neural networks for predicting robot commands falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Lastly, the paper deals with real-time control of a robot, which could also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
